properties.name: Reigate
properties.wheelchair:description: Platform 1 for Gatwick: Step free via side gate to ticket office & WC, Platform 2 for Reading & London step free, Blue Badge Bays nearby. Hearing Loop in Booking Office. Uneven "Step-free" to town is across rail tracks. Subway has steps.

properties.name: Dalston Junction
properties.wheelchair:description: Wide gates, lift down to all plaforms, Radar key operated wheelchair accessible toilet near lift at ticket hall level. Step-free from platform to train.

properties.name: Westminster
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts link all platforms on Jubilee and Circle/District lines. (photos to follow)

properties.name: Balham
properties.wheelchair:description: LU station not accessible. However, NR station is step-free to platform via the LU entrance.

properties.name: Old Street
properties.wheelchair:description: Steps between lower Northern & higher National Rail station levels. No Lifts.

properties.name: West Croydon
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free from street to Overground platform. Ramp to bridge for other platforms. On demand platform to train portable ramps.

properties.name: East Croydon
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts from West entrance & ramps from main George Street concourse to all platforms. Accessible WCs not checked today.

properties.name: Station to Flower Show
properties.wheelchair:description: Down three flights of steps from highway.

properties.name: Horley
properties.wheelchair:description: Accessible WC in ticket office on Victoria Road, also step-free to Bus Stops A & B. (upper level). Lifts to all platforms. Step-free entrance to platform 1 from car park.

properties.name: Edgware Road (Circle, District and Hammersmith & City lines)
properties.wikipedia: en:Edgware Road tube station (Circle, District and Hammersmith & City lines)

properties.name: Turks Pier Hampton Court
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free, very steep path from landing stage. Loading access not checked. Turks Facebook page says this is boat accessible.

properties.name: Rotherhithe
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free from platform to train

properties.name: Surrey Quays
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free from platform to train

properties.name: Wapping
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free from platform to train. (NOT shown Step-free from street on 2017 TfL map)

properties.name: Salfords
properties.wheelchair:description: Only Northbound platform 1 has step free access. Southbound platform 2 via bridge. Blue Badge space by station entrance. WC on platform 1 not checked as it was locked (June 2018)

properties.name: Earlswood
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free to northbound platform only. No barriers. Stairs and subway to southbound. (WC not checked today) one Blue Badge space and dipped kerb opposite entrances.

properties.name: Hampton
properties.note: Platform 1 is Clapham Junction and London Waterloo bound; Platform 2 is Shepperton bound

properties.name: Amersham
properties.source: aerial imagery, GPS and interpolation from bridge.

properties.name: Chalfont & Latimer
properties.note: Chiltern Line and Metropolitan Line Station

properties.name: Merstham
properties.wheelchair:description: No access from Platform 1, Booking office and car park to Platform 2 (towards Gatwick and coast). Train ramp NOT available all day. Loop not working (3/16)

properties.name: Sutton
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts to all platforms. Accessible toilets on Platforms 1 & 2/3. Also ChangingPlaces Toilet on 2/3. http://changingplaces.uktoiletmap.org/toilet/view/620 - Station supervisor is able to offer a key to non-travellers.

properties.name: Seer Green and Jordans
properties.wikipedia: en:Seer Green and Jordans railway station

properties.name: Shadwell
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free from platform to train

properties.name: Betchworth
properties.wheelchair:description: Unstaffed station, ramps available for use by train crew. Steep ramps up onto platforms both sides. Gate to Gatwick trains easy to open. Nearby road has no footway.

properties.name: Woking
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts at west end footbridge. Accessible toilets on platforms 3/4 & 5 (1/2 not checked for toilet). Some dedicated Blue Badge spaces near south entrance.

properties.name: Blackfriars
properties.wheelchair:description: Lift to platform, step-free onto trains (Only Eastbound checked and photos today)

properties.name: London Victoria
properties.wheelchair:description: Concourse to platforms step-free & wide gates. Access to all trains by portable ramps, no Harrington Humps discovered yet.

properties.name: Dorking
properties.wheelchair:description: Automatic sliding doors from street to ticket hall & platform 1. Lift to bridge for terminal platforms 2 & 3. Manual ramps. Toilets not yet checked.

properties.name: Dorking Deepdene
properties.wheelchair:description: Unstaffed. Long flights of steps from both platforms to Road for interchange with Dorking North station.

properties.name: Redhill
properties.wheelchair:description: Blue Badge spaces (2). Ramps to ticket office and tactile map of station. Lifts to all platforms. Accessible toilet (RADAR KEY) on Platform 3. Defibrillator in subway by lift to platforms 1+2.

properties.name: Bexley
properties.wheelchair:description: Only the near platform (to Crayford) is accessible

properties.name: Lewisham DLR
properties.wheelchair:description: DLR fully accessible

properties.name: West Ruislip
properties.source: NPE, and wikipedia description for which goes on which side

properties.name: Box Hill & Westhumble
properties.wheelchair:description: Unstaffed station. Step-free to southbound Platform 2. Footbridge only access to northbound Platform 1 towards London. One Dedicated Blue Badge space in free parking area.

properties.name: Hampton Court
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free between platforms & to Hampton Court via east side of bridge. Nearest controlled crossing by station entrance NOT step-free. WC not checked today.

properties.name: Flower show to Park and Ride bus
properties.note: In 2017 only one of three ferries had wheelchair carrying capability
properties.wheelchair:description: Bridge to pontoon has steps both ends. 2017 Show: Only one of three ferries claimed to be wheelchair accessible.

properties.name: Canada Water
properties.wheelchair:description: Overground platforms Step-free to train. (Jubilee platforms need checking)

properties.name: Leatherhead
properties.wheelchair:description: Ramp to Booking Office entrance west side, for London, manual doors. Accessible toilet (key). Long roadside ramps to east side platform. Hearing Loop.

properties.name: Guildford
properties.source:name: Local knowledge
properties.wheelchair:description: NOT Step-free from west side. One low counter at booking office, but seen shut on several visits. Ramped route to all platforms. Accessible toilet on platform 2B, near ramp.

properties.name: New Cross Gate
properties.wheelchair:description: Step down from train to platform

properties.name: Dartford
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts to all platforms

properties.name: Norwood Junction
properties.wheelchair:description: To access any platforms except platform 1 there is only stair access. There are about 15 stairs to access the platforms.

properties.name: Sunningdale
properties.note: On this railway station customers have to show their rail ticket at the ticket office to get the code for using the toilets.

properties.name: Addlestone
properties.wheelchair:description: Both platforms accessible by ramps from street. Only automatic ticket sales. Access to opposite platform via level crossing.

properties.name: Teddington
properties.source:name: local knowledge
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access to both platforms from street but bridge between platforms not wheelchair accessible.

properties.name: Elverson Road
properties.wheelchair:description: Flat access from platform to train. Bridge to other platform has steps and long, shallow easily navegable ramp. No toilet.

properties.name: Deptford Bridge
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access from platform to train. Access to platform via small lift or stairs. No toilets.

properties.name: Custom House for ExCeL
properties.wheelchair:description: Alle von uns benutzten DLR-Stationen (Docklands Light Railway) waren mit Aufzügen ausgestattet. Der Zugang vom Bahnsteig in die Züge ist mit dem Rollstuhl problemlos möglich.
properties.wikipedia: en:Custom House for ExCeL DLR Station

properties.wikipedia: en:Hammersmith tube station (District and Piccadilly lines)

properties.description: The station has Wheelchair Access to the ticket office & platforms, although stairs connect the two. To get between them, the accessible route involves a footpath through the car park.

properties.name: High Street Kensington
properties.wheelchair:description: Step access only to all platforms from booking office and gateline.

properties.name: Gloucester Road
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free from train to Circle line platforms 2 & 3 to view Mural on north retaining wall. Stairs only between platforms and to booking office and gateline.

properties.name: Goodge Street
properties.wheelchair:description: No level access

properties.name: Highbury & Islington
properties.wheelchair:description: Level street access. Lifts from concourse to Overground platforms (1,2,7,8) + portable ramps. Escalators, then stairs to Victoria and GN platforms (3,4,5,6) No interchange underground.

properties.name: Harpenden
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts from platform to footbridge. Step-free exit from platform 1 to car park on east side.

properties.name: Shoreditch High Street
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free from platform to train. (TfL map shows fully Step-free)
